3. In these Regulations - 

“Act” means the Vehicle Clamping Act 2015; 

“appellant” means a person who brings a section 22 appeal; 

“letter of determination” means the written determination of an appeal by a 
parking controller under section 20(5) of the Act; 

“section 22 appeal” means an appeal to a clamping appeals officer under section 
22 of the Act. 

APPEALS TO THE CLAMPING APPEALS OFFICER 

Part 2 

Procedures for a section 22 appeal
